			<div class="blog-faq"><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
				<div class="faq-item"><h3>How long do plastic surgery results typically last?</h3><p>Results vary by procedure. Many provide long-lasting or permanent results, though natural aging continues. Maintaining a healthy lifestyle and proper skincare helps extend the longevity of your results significantly.</p></div>
				<div class="faq-item"><h3>Can I exercise after plastic surgery? How soon?</h3><p>Yes, exercise is encouraged but timing varies by procedure. Most patients can resume light activity within weeks and full exercise within several months. Always follow your surgeon's specific guidelines for your procedure.</p></div>
				<div class="faq-item"><h3>How important is sun protection after surgery?</h3><p>Sun protection is extremely important. UV radiation accelerates aging, worsens scarring, and damages skin. Wearing SPF 30+ sunscreen daily and avoiding tanning beds are essential for preserving your results.</p></div>
				<div class="faq-item"><h3>Will I need touch-up procedures in the future?</h3><p>Some patients eventually desire minor touch-ups as they age, but many are satisfied for years or decades. Touch-ups can range from non-surgical treatments to minor surgical refinements and are completely normal.</p></div>
				<div class="faq-item"><h3>What skincare products are best after plastic surgery?</h3><p>Your surgeon will recommend specific products during recovery. In the long term, a routine with gentle cleansers, moisturizers, retinoids, vitamin C, and sunscreen helps maintain surgical results and skin health.</p></div>
				<div class="faq-item"><h3>How often should I see my surgeon after recovery?</h3><p>Most surgeons recommend annual or bi-annual check-ups after the initial recovery period. These visits help monitor your results and provide early detection of any changes that may benefit from treatment.</p></div>
				<div class="faq-item"><h3>Does weight change affect plastic surgery results?</h3><p>Significant weight changes can alter results from body contouring and breast procedures. Maintaining a stable weight through diet and exercise is one of the best ways to preserve your surgical investment.</p></div>
